The <strong><code>SourceBuffer</code></strong> interface represents a chunk of media to be passed into an <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLMediaElement" title="The HTMLMediaElement interface adds to HTMLElement the properties and methods needed to support basic media-related capabilities that are common to audio and video."><code>HTMLMediaElement</code></a> and played, via a <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/API/MediaSource" title="The MediaSource interface of the Media Source Extensions API represents a source of media data for an HTMLMediaElement object. A MediaSource object can be attached to a HTMLMediaElement to be played in the user agent."><code>MediaSource</code></a> object. This can be made up of one or several media segments.